From 4d6ab9af5b0a16870a2799d067c82ce3d7974c1b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jan Nieuwenhuizen <janneke@gnu.org>
Date: Tue, 4 Feb 2020 09:32:15 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] DRAFT ltscompare: add -x,--structured-output option.

Instead of human readable chatter, write line-based, structured, ascii
result to stdout.  Also, do not clutter file system with counter
examples.

Use exit code to report equality, like we expect from tools like diff.
